      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for the draft. I just ran it through the tool and the score was actually pretty low—it's flagging it as being too \"corporate\" or \"distant.\" \n\nThe score is mostly because the pronoun count is low. Can you try another version that feels a bit more personal? I'm still stressing that you shouldn't make it weird or unprofessional, but you definitely need to bump up that score so it actually passes the internal check. Try to make it feel more like a 1-on-1 conversation.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course! Here's an improved draft that should enhance the sense of personal connection:\n\nSubject: 🌟 Exciting Senior Backend Engineer Opportunity Awaits (Just For You) 🌟\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI hope this message resonates well with you as I reach out from [Your Company Name]. I've taken a particular interest in your detailed profile, and it aligns perfectly with our team's ongoing projects focusing on distributed systems with a strong emphasis on scalability and high-throughput microservices.\n\nAs a seasoned professional with a profound passion for backend engineering, your expertise in Go, Rust, and Kubernetes would significantly contribute to building the cutting-edge systems we've envisioned. Our aim always is to work closely with distinguished engineers like yourself to continually innovate and push the boundaries.\n\nWe are eager to hear more about your journey and the potential ways your skills and mindset align with us. I genuinely believe there's a perfect match waiting to be discovered.\n\nIf this sounds intriguing, let's connect. I'm looking forward to possibly discussing how together we could craft a remarkable synergy.\n\nWarm Regards,\n[Your Full Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Your Contact Information] \n\n\"Subject: [1-on-1 opportunity for a Senior Backend Engineer at [Your Company Name]] // Let's Connect and Build Together\"\n\nThere",
      "source": "target",
